-- MSCI declares first-ever dividend, hikes stock buyback plan
-- 
-- Thu Sep 18, 2014 08:04AM EDT
-- None



Sept 18 (Reuters) - Stock market indexes provider MSCI Inc <MSCI.N> declared its first-ever quarterly dividend and more than doubled its stock repurchase program to $850 million from $300 million.

The company said the buyback - which includes a $300 million accelerated share repurchase agreement with Goldman Sachs <GS.N> - and the dividend would return about $1 billion to shareholders by the end of 2016. [ID:nBw637yt9a]